## Real-Time Analytics

### Streaming Market Data

```python
class RealTimeAnalyticsProcessor:
    async def process_market_data_stream(self, data: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict:
        symbol = data['symbol']
        price = data['price']
        
        # Maintain rolling buffer
        self.buffer[symbol]['prices'].append(price)
        
        # Calculate real-time metrics
        if len(self.buffer[symbol]['prices']) >= 20:
            returns = self._calculate_returns(self.buffer[symbol]['prices'])
            volatility = np.std(returns[-20:]) * np.sqrt(252)
            momentum = (price - self.buffer[symbol]['prices'][-10]) / self.buffer[symbol]['prices'][-10]
        
        return {
            'current_price': price,
            'volatility': volatility,
            'momentum': momentum
        }
```

